      },
      {
        "from": "payment-service",
        "to": "postgresql",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "Connection pool of 10 with no retry logic. Pool size is half the worker thread count (20), meaning under normal load 10 threads may already be starved. Zero retry means any transient connection failure is a hard failure for that payment."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "Service configuration has a fundamental mismatch: 20 worker threads but only 10 DB connections means the DB is a bottleneck by design. Stripe timeout (10s) is 5x the fraud timeout (2s), creating uneven backpressure characteristics.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "Critical path is: request → fraud check → Stripe charge → DB write. All three dependencies are serial with no compensation mechanism (saga, outbox, etc.) visible. A failure after Stripe charge but before DB write could result in a charged customer with no transaction record."
