    "circuit_breakers": "Only on Stripe (5-failure threshold, 60s reset). None on fraud detection service — this is a critical gap. No latency-based circuit breaking anywhere — Scenario C proves this gap is exploitable.",
    "graceful_degradation": "None. Every dependency is treated as hard — if any single one fails, the entire payment fails with no fallback, no queueing, and no partial functionality. No load shedding, no admission control, no bulkheading."
